==English==
=== Etymology ===
From the Latin ''[[claustrum]]'' "a shut in place," from ''[[claudere]]'' "to close" + Greek ''[[phobos]]'' "fear."  First attested in the British Medical Journal

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-əʊbiə|-əʊbiə]]

===Noun===
'''claustrophobia'''
# the [[fear]] of [[closed]], [[tight]] places

